<Reset>

# go to the one before HEAD
$ git reset HEAD^(master^) or $ git reset HEAD~1

# go to the x before HEAD
$ git reset HEAD~x

# go to 85e7e30 
$ git reset 85e7e30

After reset, there are (files/deleted steps) that are departed by you 
So, there are three modes 

--mixed
This is default mode, and this will make your departed files go to the work directory

--soft
This will make your files go to the staging area

--hard
Discard all the files departed.
